                            <!-- <h2><span class="font-Trajan font-size-40">FONDART BAKEHOUSE</span></h2> -->
                            <h2><span class="font-Zapfino font-size-80">The Fab Story</span></h2>
                            <p class="font-Tnr font-size-20">
                            
                            Fondart Bakehouse, fondly known as FAB, patisserie and boulangerie opened its doors to people of Lucknow in April 2021. FAB is the brainchild of founders Nidhi Verma and Raag Verma, who have been associated with the luxury hospitality industry for nearly two decades. <br /><br />
                            The name of this patisserie in Lucknow, is inspired from its signature offering - fondant cakes. These specialised playdough-like sugar paste can be rolled and draped over a sculpted cake to give it a designer shape and texture. These cakes can be refrigerated and can remain fresh for days, which is what makes them unique. <br /><br />
                            It specialises in custom cakes, baked in Lucknow, for all occasions along with sinful delights comprising an array of freshly baked bread varieties, pastries, cupcakes, truffles, croissants, macaroons, eclairs and donuts. It will also offer a several options for sandwiches, quiches and its signature croissants. According to co-founder Nidhi Verma, FAB is positioned as Lucknow’s first luxury and premium patisserie and boulangerie catering to the city’s up-market and mid-segment clientele. <br /><br />
                            “Our innovative, premium quality products will be one of its kind in Lucknow. The bakery will also accommodate private parties and offer cake and cupcake decorating classes to the local community,” added Nidhi about this upscale patisserie in Lucknow. <br /><br />
                            What you will find here is the most freshly baked cakes, pastries, variety of breads, savories, customised cakes for occasions and celebrations. <br /><br />
                            They are also on online home delivery platforms.
                            </p>
                        
